# 2p_bot_frag_charge — HOST (stationary target). M6 P13.
#
# A Champion-tier bot, added by the client via `add_bot`, faces this
# host across ~1800 px on Aurora's central flat floor. The bot's
# loadout (Pulse Rifle + Frag Grenades) is the default for index 0
# at tier ≥ Veteran, so the off-hand frag is the WFIRE_THROW path
# under test. Pre-M6-P13 the bot fired BTN_FIRE_SECONDARY through
# the existing 5-on/5-off duty cycle and threw at ~0.08 charge
# (350 px/s lobs). Post-fix the motor holds the button for the
# tier × distance target charge (Champion ≥ 0.9 at 1800 px), the
# release-edge in mech_try_fire fires at ~2700 px/s, and the
# grenade arcs across the gap.
#
# Host plays passive — fixed spawn, neutral aim, no fire. The bot
# is mech_id 2; we use `peer_spawn 2` so the bot lands at a known
# x and the test geometry is deterministic. The client (mech_id 1)
# parks far enough away that the bot's nearest-enemy selection
# locks onto host first.

window 1600 900
out build/shots/net/2p_bot_frag_charge_host
network host 24320
name HostA
map aurora

loadout - "Pulse Rifle" "Sidearm" Light Standard

# Aurora central floor sits at y=2712. Host at x=1700 (target);
# client far away to bias bot's target selection toward host.
# Slot assignment (cfg bot-fill runs at host bootstrap, before any
# client connects): 0=host, 1=bot, 2=client.
spawn_at 1700 2712
peer_spawn 1 3500 2712
peer_spawn 2 5500 2712

# Neutral aim so the host doesn't fire forward; bot ignores us not
# shooting back.
aim 1800 2712

# === captures (shared names with the client script for side-by-side
#     compositing) ===
at 120 shot t120_match_start
at 200 shot t200_charge_1
at 260 shot t260_throw_1
at 320 shot t320_impact_1
at 380 shot t380_charge_2
at 440 shot t440_throw_2
at 500 shot t500_charge_3
at 560 shot t560_throw_3
at 620 shot t620_aftermath

contact_sheet bot_frag_charge_host cols 5

at 720 end
